  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "What I am worried about is that we already have four methods to set `attributes` on the html:\n- cssClass\n- rootClass\n- itemClass\n- htmlAttributes\n\nSo we need to find what is necessary and then provide it.\n\nMaybe we should just have htmlAttributes but automatically adding attributes to a namespace that is managed and used by react is maybe dangerous.\n\nFrom our discussions I understood that the need for `htmlAttributes` was motivated by the fact that to generate a `select` with the corresponding `label` we needed to provide the `id` of the select.\n\nIf `htmlAttributes` is only here to be able to add an `id` and if that's the only need we have right now. Then I would automatically add an `id` in all our widgets based on the widget name:\n\n`ais-sortIndex-1` something like that.\n\nThis should be sufficient if the only need that we can think of right now is adding an `id`. We would then see if we really need anything else like `htmlAttributes`.\n",
